<dl id="n53131b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53131b">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53131b"> 131(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 2 boy come yesterday</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Jespersen cites Peano, the Italian originator of a language he termed <i>Latine sine flexione</i>, to the effect that in the statement &lsquo;two boys came yesterday&rsquo;, there is a redundant duplication of both the plural and the time elements. Peano would have us put it, &lsquo;<mark>two boy come yesterday</mark>&rsquo;.]</font> <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJIL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OJIL"><cite title="source">An International Language</cite></a> (1928) 47</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
